## Overview
Add a subtle 3D perspective tilt to tool cards on hover, similar to Apple's product cards, creating depth and premium feel.

## Reference
- apple.com product cards
- stripe.com/atlas feature cards
- Linear.app feature showcase

## Proposed Effect
- Card tilts toward cursor position (max ~5 degrees)
- Subtle parallax between layers (icon moves slightly more)
- Gentle shine/reflection moves across surface
- Smooth return to flat on mouse leave

## Technical Implementation

### Basic Tilt with Vanilla-Tilt
```tsx
import VanillaTilt from 'vanilla-tilt';

useEffect(() => {
  if (cardRef.current && !reducedMotion) {
    VanillaTilt.init(cardRef.current, {
      max: 5,
      speed: 400,
      glare: true,
      'max-glare': 0.1,
      perspective: 1000,
    });
  }
  return () => cardRef.current?.vanillaTilt?.destroy();
}, [reducedMotion]);
```

### Custom Implementation (No Dependency)
```tsx
function use3DTilt(ref: RefObject<HTMLElement>, options = {}) {
  const { max = 5, perspective = 1000 } = options;

  useEffect(() => {
    const el = ref.current;
    if (!el) return;

    const handleMouseMove = (e: MouseEvent) => {
      const rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
      const x = e.clientX - rect.left;
      const y = e.clientY - rect.top;

      const centerX = rect.width / 2;
      const centerY = rect.height / 2;

      const rotateX = ((y - centerY) / centerY) * -max;
      const rotateY = ((x - centerX) / centerX) * max;

      el.style.transform = `
        perspective(${perspective}px)
        rotateX(${rotateX}deg)
        rotateY(${rotateY}deg)
        scale3d(1.02, 1.02, 1.02)
      `;
    };

    const handleMouseLeave = () => {
      el.style.transform = 'perspective(1000px) rotateX(0) rotateY(0) scale3d(1, 1, 1)';
      el.style.transition = 'transform 0.5s ease-out';
    };

    el.addEventListener('mousemove', handleMouseMove);
    el.addEventListener('mouseleave', handleMouseLeave);

    return () => {
      el.removeEventListener('mousemove', handleMouseMove);
      el.removeEventListener('mouseleave', handleMouseLeave);
    };
  }, [ref, max, perspective]);
}
```

### Parallax Layers
```tsx
// Icon moves slightly more than card for depth
const iconParallax = {
  x: rotateY * 0.5, // Extra movement
  y: rotateX * 0.5,
};

<div style={{ transform: `translate(${iconParallax.x}px, ${iconParallax.y}px)` }}>
  <ToolIcon />
</div>
```

## Visual Enhancements

### Shine/Glare Effect
```css
.card-shine {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: linear-gradient(
    105deg,
    transparent 40%,
    rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03) 45%,
    rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05) 50%,
    rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03) 55%,
    transparent 60%
  );
  transform: translateX(-100%);
  transition: transform 0.5s ease-out;
}

.card:hover .card-shine {
  transform: translateX(100%);
}
```

### Shadow Enhancement
```tsx
// Shadow moves opposite to tilt for realism
const shadowX = -rotateY * 2;
const shadowY = rotateX * 2;

style={{
  boxShadow: `
    ${shadowX}px ${shadowY}px 30px -10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3),
    0 10px 20px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2)
  `
}}
```

## Files to Modify
- `components/tldr-tool-card.tsx` - Add tilt effect
- May need `hooks/use-3d-tilt.ts` if custom implementation

## Performance Considerations
- Use `transform` and `opacity` only (GPU accelerated)
- Add `will-change: transform` before hover
- Remove `will-change` after mouse leave
- Throttle mousemove handler (requestAnimationFrame)

## Reduced Motion
